<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}-{8}{y}={64}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}-{4}{y}={40}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{4},-{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{8}{y}={64}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={64}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{64}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{\left(\frac{{{64}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}\right)}+-{4}{y}={40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{4}}{{-{{4}}}}\cdot{\left({64}\right)}--\frac{{4}}{{-{{4}}}}{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}+-{4}{y}={40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{64}-{\left({8}\right)}{y}+-{4}{y}={40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{y}+{\left(-{4}\right)}{y}={40}-{64}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{y}+{\left(-{4}\right)}{y}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({8}+{\left(-{4}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{y}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{24}}{{4}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{8}{\left(-{6}\right)}={64}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{\left({48}\right)}={64}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={64}-{\left({48}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{16}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{4},-{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
